WEBVTT

00:06.186 --> 00:08.353
<i>(UPBEAT ROCKABILLY MUSIC)</i>

00:08.355 --> 00:11.823
<i>♪ Train I ride ♪</i>

00:11.825 --> 00:14.826
<i>♪ 16 coaches long ♪</i>

00:14.828 --> 00:18.546
<i>♪</i>

00:18.549 --> 00:22.333
<i>♪ Train I ride ♪</i>

00:22.335 --> 00:25.370
<i>♪ 16 coaches long ♪</i>

00:25.372 --> 00:27.683
<i>♪</i>

00:27.686 --> 00:30.375
<i>♪ Well, that long black train ♪</i>

00:30.377 --> 00:33.211
<i>♪ Got my baby and gone ♪</i>

00:33.213 --> 00:36.381
<i>♪</i>

00:36.383 --> 00:38.632
<i>♪ Train, train ♪</i>

00:38.635 --> 00:39.601
- Hey.
- Hey.

00:39.604 --> 00:41.370
What can I get you?

00:41.373 --> 00:43.321
I'm a sucker for a sidecar on a train.

00:43.323 --> 00:46.124
Guys, this is not a subway car!

00:46.126 --> 00:47.959
- MAN: All right, sorry.
- (SCOFFS)

00:47.961 --> 00:49.959
MAN: Sorry.

00:49.962 --> 00:51.561
Did you know at a Ukrainian wedding,

00:51.564 --> 00:53.531
the bride has to keep her shoes on?

00:53.534 --> 00:55.502
'Cause otherwise the
guests will steal them

00:55.505 --> 00:56.834
and drink wine out of them.

00:56.836 --> 00:58.174
It's good luck.

00:58.177 --> 00:59.621
Well, unless I missed a few stops,

00:59.624 --> 01:03.192
I'm pretty sure we are not
about to roll into Kiev.

01:03.195 --> 01:04.525
So...

01:04.528 --> 01:06.161
now I get to ask you the question

01:06.164 --> 01:08.382
that I ask everyone on here:

01:08.385 --> 01:09.847
why the train?

01:09.849 --> 01:11.249
Spent a lot of time in Europe,

01:11.251 --> 01:13.084
fell in love with train travel.

01:13.086 --> 01:14.385
Yeah, but this is Phoenix to LA.

01:14.387 --> 01:16.621
It isn't exactly the Orient Express.

01:16.623 --> 01:18.323
Well, Phoenix is home

01:18.325 --> 01:21.893
and LA used to be home, so.

01:21.895 --> 01:24.968
Somebody waiting for you there?

01:24.971 --> 01:27.265
No.

01:27.267 --> 01:30.201
He stopped waiting
for me a long time ago.

01:30.203 --> 01:32.970
- Summer camp?
- It's all he can talk about.

01:32.972 --> 01:35.973
Some of the other kids
from school are going.

01:35.975 --> 01:38.176
It's only two weeks.

01:38.178 --> 01:39.344
- Time.
- Whoa, whoa.

01:39.346 --> 01:41.277
Two weeks away from home?

01:41.280 --> 01:43.013
Isn't Chris kind of young for that?

01:43.016 --> 01:44.349
I mean, what if something happens?

01:44.351 --> 01:45.702
What if he gets homesick?

01:45.705 --> 01:46.963
I'm pretty sure I
brought in the brochure

01:46.965 --> 01:49.055
so you guys can make me
feel better about him going.

01:49.058 --> 01:51.040
Clearly, you did not
think that plan through

01:51.043 --> 01:52.705
to its logical conclusion.

01:52.708 --> 01:54.791
I started going to
sleepaway camp when I was 8.

01:54.794 --> 01:57.462
I loved it. Camp Weegeewagen.

01:57.464 --> 01:59.997
Eedee-idee-odee-ooh-hoo!

01:59.999 --> 02:02.311
Looked forward to it every year.

02:02.314 --> 02:04.534
Yeah, but Christopher's a city kid.

02:04.537 --> 02:06.137
So was I.

02:06.139 --> 02:08.872
St. Paul is a city.

02:08.875 --> 02:11.309
- If you say so.
- (LAUGHTER)

02:11.311 --> 02:13.411
I'm just trying to imagine
trying to sell Denny

02:13.413 --> 02:16.226
on the idea of two weeks
without the internet.

02:16.229 --> 02:17.695
It's pretty exciting.

02:17.698 --> 02:19.364
They even have this farm-to-fork program

02:19.367 --> 02:21.919
where the kids pick veggies
and cook 'em for dinner.

02:21.921 --> 02:25.156
That sounds a lot like child labor.

02:25.158 --> 02:27.592
(SIGHS) Okay.

02:27.594 --> 02:30.428
<i>(ANXIOUS MUSIC)</i>

02:30.430 --> 02:36.934
<i>♪</i>

02:36.936 --> 02:38.136
Damn it!

02:38.138 --> 02:39.871
Hmm.

02:39.873 --> 02:42.473
I gotta get above a 511.

02:42.475 --> 02:45.260
504 is pretty good.

02:45.263 --> 02:46.595
Getting into medical school

02:46.598 --> 02:48.211
at this point in my life is hard enough.

02:48.214 --> 02:51.182
I can't afford to be
an average applicant.

02:51.184 --> 02:53.851
Hey, there is nothing average about you.

02:53.854 --> 02:56.253
You just started studying
this. Give yourself a break.

02:56.256 --> 02:57.422
Yeah. Hey, come on.

02:57.424 --> 02:59.390
You are gonna rock the MCATs.

02:59.392 --> 03:06.298
<i>♪</i>

03:07.967 --> 03:09.434
Hen, you're brilliant.

03:09.436 --> 03:11.536
You don't need a test to prove that.

03:11.538 --> 03:14.362
(PHONE CHIMES)

03:14.365 --> 03:17.542
Bobby, why is your wife asking me

03:17.544 --> 03:21.045
if she could hold May's graduation party

03:21.047 --> 03:23.514
at my house?

03:23.516 --> 03:27.018
Our living room is kind of
under construction right now.

03:27.020 --> 03:28.920
I'm in the hospital for four days

03:28.922 --> 03:31.393
and you two lose your damn mind!

03:31.396 --> 03:32.662
I told you, Athena.

03:32.665 --> 03:34.225
I was trying to make Bobby feel better.

03:34.227 --> 03:36.227
What about making me feel better?

03:36.229 --> 03:37.829
I'm the one with the broken arm

03:37.831 --> 03:40.330
and 50 people coming
for a party in two weeks.

03:40.333 --> 03:42.133
I didn't think we were
still having a party, Mom.

03:42.135 --> 03:43.133
You just got out of the hospital.

03:43.135 --> 03:44.928
May, you are graduating
from high school.

03:44.931 --> 03:47.473
There will be a party
and a cake and photographs

03:47.476 --> 03:50.240
with a fireplace that does
not look like a pile of rubble.

03:50.243 --> 03:51.809
Are you gonna finish taking it down?

03:51.811 --> 03:53.244
- 'Cause I can help.
- No, no, no.

03:53.246 --> 03:55.346
You will not. Your father broke it.

03:55.348 --> 03:56.679
He's gonna fix it.

03:56.682 --> 03:58.848
- Absolutely. Okay?
- (PHONE CHIMES)

03:58.851 --> 04:01.551
I'm gonna go home, do some sketches,

04:01.554 --> 04:03.955
and I will come back
here in the morning, okay?

04:03.957 --> 04:06.891
Good, 'cause Hen says there's
not enough room at her place

04:06.893 --> 04:08.320
for parking for all of our guests.

04:08.323 --> 04:09.340
Okay, this is silly.

04:09.343 --> 04:10.826
We really don't need to have a party.

04:10.829 --> 04:13.063
Since when don't you wanna have a party?

04:13.066 --> 04:15.898
Dad, don't you have a doctor's
appointment in the morning?

04:15.901 --> 04:19.269
ATHENA: Michael.

04:19.272 --> 04:21.004
Your results are in.

04:21.007 --> 04:22.473
You want me to come with you?

04:22.475 --> 04:24.675
No. No, Athena, I got it.

04:24.677 --> 04:27.011
The doctor is gonna go
over the scans with me

04:27.013 --> 04:30.466
and, you know, then we'll know

04:30.469 --> 04:33.204
what's...

04:33.207 --> 04:34.475
what's next.

04:34.478 --> 04:36.345
Good news.

04:36.348 --> 04:39.215
That's what's next.

04:39.218 --> 04:42.386
True that.

04:42.389 --> 04:43.961
<i>MADDIE: It's good.</i>

04:43.963 --> 04:45.963
I did a lot of research, you know,

04:45.965 --> 04:48.432
on the dos and don'ts of making
a victim impact statement.

04:48.434 --> 04:49.667
I totally believe that.

04:49.669 --> 04:52.169
It's very thorough.

04:52.171 --> 04:54.472
- It's terrible, isn't it?
- No.

04:54.474 --> 04:56.173
Look, when I read this,

04:56.175 --> 04:58.643
I know exactly what Greg did to you.

04:58.645 --> 05:01.412
What I don't understand is how you...

05:01.414 --> 05:03.548
feel about any of it.

05:03.551 --> 05:05.616
Does it matter?

05:05.618 --> 05:08.519
(SIGHS) What do you think?

05:08.521 --> 05:11.322
I mean, is this really
what you wanna say to him?

05:11.324 --> 05:13.057
I think the judge would discourage

05:13.059 --> 05:14.892
the use of curse words.

05:14.894 --> 05:17.495
Okay, so then...

05:17.497 --> 05:19.327
find new words.

05:19.330 --> 05:20.796
Your words.

05:20.799 --> 05:23.500
Look, this moment is about you.

05:23.503 --> 05:26.637
It's not about what
you're supposed to say.

05:26.639 --> 05:28.039
It should come from your heart.

05:28.041 --> 05:31.042
<i>(EMOTIONAL MUSIC)</i>

05:31.044 --> 05:33.078
<i>♪</i>

05:34.480 --> 05:36.180
(YAWNS) I am so sorry.

05:36.182 --> 05:38.215
- That...
- (BOTH LAUGH)

05:38.217 --> 05:40.551
That had nothing to
do with you, I promise.

05:40.553 --> 05:43.888
I am trying not to be offended.

05:43.890 --> 05:46.290
I just need to refill.

05:46.292 --> 05:49.328
<i>(UPBEAT MUSIC)</i>

05:51.130 --> 05:55.466
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS)

05:55.468 --> 05:58.970
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

05:58.972 --> 06:03.341
<i>♪</i>

06:03.343 --> 06:04.675
MAN: Really?

06:04.677 --> 06:07.211
<i>♪</i>

06:07.213 --> 06:09.046
Really?

06:09.048 --> 06:10.681
'Scuse me.

06:10.683 --> 06:13.517
Look, man, self-expression
is kind of my right, okay?

06:13.519 --> 06:16.475
Not when it infringes on
my right to peace and quiet.

06:16.478 --> 06:18.623
Look, I got a huge show
at the Roxy, all right?

06:18.626 --> 06:20.611
- I don't care!
- Okay, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

06:20.614 --> 06:22.580
Why don't we hit the pause
button here, all right?

06:22.583 --> 06:23.592
I think a little peace and quiet

06:23.594 --> 06:24.828
would be a great idea all around.

06:24.830 --> 06:26.506
She doesn't have a pause button.

06:28.801 --> 06:31.302
- (METAL CLUNKING)
- (ELECTRICITY ZAPPING)

06:31.304 --> 06:33.337
That's not good.

06:33.339 --> 06:36.007
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS)

06:36.009 --> 06:38.143
Come on, man. She's a kid.

06:39.979 --> 06:41.779
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

06:41.781 --> 06:43.047
MAN: What the hell is that?

06:43.050 --> 06:44.515
(WHISTLE BLOWING)

06:44.517 --> 06:47.885
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

06:47.887 --> 06:49.086
(PEOPLE GASPING)

06:49.088 --> 06:51.088
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

06:51.090 --> 06:52.456
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

06:52.458 --> 06:54.625
(GLASS SHATTERING)

06:54.627 --> 06:57.261
(METAL SCREECHING)

06:57.263 --> 06:59.630
<i>♪</i>

06:59.632 --> 07:02.600
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

07:02.602 --> 07:05.536
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

07:05.538 --> 07:08.089
_

07:08.092 --> 07:14.177
<i>♪</i>

07:14.180 --> 07:16.414
(GRUNTS) Now. Try it again.

07:16.416 --> 07:18.215
(ENGINE TURNING OVER)

07:18.217 --> 07:19.710
- Oh... ha-ha!
- Hey!

07:19.713 --> 07:21.218
There you go!

07:21.220 --> 07:24.055
(LAUGHS)

07:24.057 --> 07:25.256
Awesome, Dad. You did it.

07:25.258 --> 07:26.590
- Not bad, right?
- Yeah.

07:26.592 --> 07:28.626
- Not bad at all.
- (BELLS DINGING)

07:28.628 --> 07:30.428
Hey! Slow down!

07:30.430 --> 07:33.431
5 MPH! 5!

07:33.433 --> 07:36.701
Morons. Kill somebody.

07:36.703 --> 07:39.203
So...

07:39.205 --> 07:41.399
now that you got it
running, what's the plan?

07:41.402 --> 07:43.001
Sneaking out when I'm not looking?

07:43.004 --> 07:44.975
Why would we do that?
We've only been here...

07:44.977 --> 07:46.377
Three nights!

07:46.379 --> 07:48.613
Three nights for which
I have not been paid.

07:50.416 --> 07:52.450
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

07:52.452 --> 07:54.018
Look, I thought we talked...

07:54.020 --> 07:55.718
RORY: Three nights is my limit.

07:55.721 --> 07:57.888
- I want you out of here.
- (TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING)

07:57.890 --> 07:59.250
You mean now?

07:59.253 --> 08:02.959
Get yourself gone, or
I will have you towed.

08:02.962 --> 08:08.933
<i>♪</i>

08:08.935 --> 08:11.435
Hey, this is... this is the last of it.

08:11.437 --> 08:13.471
There's a food bank
not too far from here.

08:13.473 --> 08:17.074
I'll... I'll hit it in the morning.

08:17.076 --> 08:18.576
Hand me a rag.

08:18.578 --> 08:21.212
Thanks.

08:21.214 --> 08:23.247
Stay inside, Milo.

08:23.249 --> 08:24.949
I'll be right back.

08:24.951 --> 08:31.389
<i>♪</i>

08:32.390 --> 08:33.823
Dude.

08:33.826 --> 08:35.458
You cannot do this to us.

08:35.461 --> 08:38.629
<i>♪</i>

08:38.631 --> 08:40.597
You told me I had a week to find a job.

08:40.600 --> 08:43.000
(LAUGHING) I never said that to you.

08:43.001 --> 08:45.635
You pay, you stay. Those are the rules.

08:45.638 --> 08:48.372
<i>♪</i>

08:48.374 --> 08:51.208
Look, I came in here

08:51.210 --> 08:54.078
because a son should never
see his father have to beg.

08:54.080 --> 08:56.046
But I'm still always telling him,

08:56.048 --> 08:58.015
"Just keep your head up.

08:58.017 --> 09:00.017
Just keep your head
up because if you don't,

09:00.019 --> 09:02.219
you won't see all the good
things that are coming."

09:02.221 --> 09:04.973
<i>(TENSE MUSIC BUILDING)</i>

09:04.976 --> 09:06.409
I don't know what's next.

09:06.412 --> 09:08.512
- What's next?
- (TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING)

09:08.515 --> 09:10.627
What's next is reality!

09:10.630 --> 09:13.264
(METAL CRASHING)

09:13.266 --> 09:16.100
(MAN SCREAMING)

09:16.102 --> 09:18.135
(METAL SCREECHING)

09:18.137 --> 09:21.338
MAN: Oh, God!

09:21.340 --> 09:24.341
(MAN MOANING)

09:24.343 --> 09:31.249
<i>♪</i>

09:32.919 --> 09:34.437
Milo!

09:39.753 --> 09:42.353
Are those all your Realtor Rapist files?

09:42.355 --> 09:44.385
Please do not call him that.

09:44.388 --> 09:45.465
Yes.

09:45.468 --> 09:47.224
I asked Lou to drop 'em off

09:47.227 --> 09:48.560
so that I could be ready for my meeting

09:48.562 --> 09:50.295
with Dr. Sanford.

09:50.297 --> 09:51.830
The victims' advocate?

09:51.832 --> 09:53.431
Mm-hmm.

09:53.433 --> 09:55.734
Going to trial, testifying in court,

09:55.736 --> 09:57.769
it can be overwhelming, so...

09:57.771 --> 10:00.947
she's gonna help all
of them get through it.

10:00.950 --> 10:02.850
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

10:02.853 --> 10:04.209
- Okay.
- Ooh, that must be her.

10:04.211 --> 10:05.376
Can I get the door?

10:05.378 --> 10:06.711
Oh, I'm fine.

10:06.713 --> 10:10.315
I still got one good arm.

10:10.317 --> 10:11.808
Ah, Dr. Sanford.

10:11.811 --> 10:13.500
Athena Grant. Come in.

10:13.503 --> 10:16.171
Thank you. And it's Kara, please.

10:16.174 --> 10:17.820
Although I'm sure my mom would want you

10:17.823 --> 10:19.289
to keep the Dr. part.

10:19.292 --> 10:21.492
It is so good to meet
you, Sergeant Grant.

10:21.495 --> 10:24.629
Oh, Athena, please. Come in.

10:24.631 --> 10:26.631
Pardon our dust.

10:26.633 --> 10:28.733
While I was out, my home turned into

10:28.735 --> 10:31.436
one of those cable remodeling shows.

10:31.438 --> 10:33.505
Surprise! It's still not done.

10:33.507 --> 10:35.306
Oh, it's a lovely home.

10:35.308 --> 10:37.576
Well, I set us up in here.

10:40.647 --> 10:42.781
You have the case files
for the other victims.

10:42.783 --> 10:43.968
Oh, yes.

10:43.971 --> 10:45.949
I'm sure you have specific questions,

10:45.952 --> 10:47.118
but I thought it would be easier

10:47.120 --> 10:48.486
to just go through all of them.

10:48.488 --> 10:51.022
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

10:51.024 --> 10:52.157
(CLEARS THROAT)

10:52.159 --> 10:54.359
Great.

10:54.361 --> 10:56.973
So...

10:56.976 --> 10:58.865
where do you wanna start?

10:59.999 --> 11:01.328
_

11:01.331 --> 11:02.766
_

11:02.769 --> 11:05.797
<i>ABBY: Pacific West 1135.</i>

11:05.800 --> 11:08.938
<i>We were heading from
Phoenix into Union Station.</i>

11:08.941 --> 11:11.975
<i>We've crashed somewhere
close to the LA County line.</i>

11:11.978 --> 11:13.260
Okay, so how many...

11:13.263 --> 11:14.674
<i>ABBY: There are multiple injuries.</i>

11:14.677 --> 11:16.544
This is a mass casualty situation.

11:16.547 --> 11:18.849
You've gotta send out
every available RA unit.

11:18.852 --> 11:21.004
We need USAR for search and rescue,

11:21.007 --> 11:23.613
LAPD for traffic control.

11:23.616 --> 11:25.611
<i>We're gonna need a
mobile command center.</i>

11:25.614 --> 11:26.969
- I'll call them now.
- Okay.

11:26.972 --> 11:29.072
<i>MADDIE: It seems like
you've done this before.</i>

11:29.075 --> 11:31.843
Yeah, but I was on
your side of the line.

11:31.846 --> 11:34.613
I used to be a 9-1-1 dispatcher.

11:34.616 --> 11:36.733
TODD: Milo!

11:36.736 --> 11:38.503
Milo, can you hear me?

11:38.505 --> 11:40.104
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

11:40.106 --> 11:47.046
<i>♪</i>

11:48.581 --> 11:51.582
(SIRENS WAILING)

11:51.585 --> 11:58.023
<i>♪</i>

11:58.971 --> 12:01.172
- Captain Bobby Nash.
- Captain Janet Reese.

12:01.175 --> 12:03.194
More houses are en route.
Search dogs as well.

12:03.196 --> 12:04.713
The debris field is pretty far and wide.

12:04.715 --> 12:06.164
We've had our hands full

12:06.166 --> 12:07.511
with all the passenger cars down here,

12:07.513 --> 12:09.451
but there are reports that
folks are trapped up there.

12:09.453 --> 12:10.668
We just can't get to 'em yet.

12:10.670 --> 12:11.913
Buck, Eddie, go have a look.

12:11.916 --> 12:13.275
See if there's a way to secure that car

12:13.277 --> 12:14.798
so we can get those people out.

12:14.814 --> 12:15.998
Is USAR on the way?

12:16.001 --> 12:18.431
Dispatch assures me a
heavy rescue is coming.

12:18.434 --> 12:20.545
All right, guys, let's
gear up. Let's go!

12:20.547 --> 12:27.286
<i>♪</i>

12:29.989 --> 12:32.556
Please, if you can just
let me up into the car.

12:32.559 --> 12:33.958
Please! I've gotta get up there.

12:33.961 --> 12:35.604
Ma'am, I'm sorry. We
can't let you inside.

12:35.607 --> 12:37.041
- It's too dangerous.
- I know it's dangerous.

12:37.043 --> 12:39.062
- I need to get up in that car.
- I hear you. I'm sorry.

12:39.064 --> 12:41.089
Wait, are you from the 118?

12:41.092 --> 12:42.291
Yeah.

12:42.294 --> 12:43.734
BUCK: Abby?

12:43.737 --> 12:46.905
<i>♪</i>

12:46.907 --> 12:48.373
Buck.

12:48.375 --> 12:51.210
<i>♪</i>

12:51.213 --> 12:53.218
- Wait, you were on the train.
- Yeah. I've gotta...

12:53.220 --> 12:54.186
We need to get you checked out.

12:54.188 --> 12:55.225
No, no, no. I'm fine.

12:55.228 --> 12:56.972
- I need to get up there.
- What? No, that's crazy!

12:56.974 --> 12:58.449
No, no, Abby, Abby, stop!

12:58.451 --> 13:02.320
I'm trying to find somebody!

13:02.322 --> 13:03.798
Okay. Well, just tell us who.

13:03.801 --> 13:06.123
- We'll go...
- My fiancé!

13:06.126 --> 13:09.458
<i>♪</i>

13:09.461 --> 13:12.262
He fell asleep and I went to the bar.

13:12.265 --> 13:15.833
Okay. Can you give us a description?

13:15.836 --> 13:17.768
That's him.

13:17.771 --> 13:19.892
We were in that top car right there,

13:19.895 --> 13:21.439
all the way in the back.

13:21.441 --> 13:24.609
<i>♪</i>

13:24.611 --> 13:26.644
We'll find him.

13:26.646 --> 13:29.461
Um...

13:29.464 --> 13:30.748
what's his name?

13:30.750 --> 13:33.318
Sam.

13:33.320 --> 13:35.253
Egan.

13:35.255 --> 13:36.750
Sam.

13:36.753 --> 13:38.520
I got it.

13:38.523 --> 13:41.056
Thank you, Buck.

13:41.059 --> 13:43.127
Oh.

13:43.129 --> 13:44.729
Don't worry about it.

13:44.731 --> 13:47.398
We'll bring him back to you.

13:47.400 --> 13:50.234
<i>♪</i>

13:50.236 --> 13:51.669
I promise.

13:51.671 --> 13:56.574
<i>♪</i>

13:56.576 --> 13:58.810
(METAL CREAKING)

13:58.812 --> 14:02.313
(GRUNTING)

14:02.315 --> 14:05.350
<i>♪</i>

14:05.352 --> 14:07.518
We got somebody.

14:07.520 --> 14:09.343
EDDIE: Cap, be advised.

14:09.346 --> 14:11.409
Another black tag up here about halfway.

14:11.412 --> 14:12.490
<i>BOBBY: Copy that.</i>

14:12.492 --> 14:18.663
<i>♪</i>

14:18.665 --> 14:20.598
(METAL CREAKING)

14:20.600 --> 14:22.266
Sam! (GRUNTS)

14:22.268 --> 14:24.068
Sam! Sam, can you hear me?

14:24.070 --> 14:25.103
(GROANS)

14:25.105 --> 14:27.105
(METAL CREAKS)

14:27.107 --> 14:29.140
- (GROANS)
- Sam.

14:29.142 --> 14:31.275
Hey, Sam.

14:31.277 --> 14:33.044
How you feeling?

14:33.046 --> 14:36.114
(GROANING) It hurts...

14:36.116 --> 14:38.649
hurts when I breathe.

14:38.651 --> 14:41.152
(WHEEZING)

14:41.154 --> 14:42.920
Please.

14:42.922 --> 14:44.689
My fiancée.

14:44.691 --> 14:47.725
She's on the train.

14:47.727 --> 14:49.293
(GROANING)

14:49.295 --> 14:50.995
Yeah, hey, hey. She's okay.

14:50.997 --> 14:54.332
(COUGHING PAINFULLY)

14:54.334 --> 14:56.167
Cap, I got a passenger pinned up here.

14:56.169 --> 14:58.736
Looks like the support beam
from the observation deck

14:58.739 --> 14:59.935
broke through the floor.

14:59.938 --> 15:01.634
Need you to send up the jaws, okay?

15:01.637 --> 15:03.307
<i>BOBBY: Copy that. Coming right up.</i>

15:03.309 --> 15:04.876
We got you, Sam.

15:04.878 --> 15:06.308
Help is on its way.

15:06.311 --> 15:09.021
- We need jaws and the ram.
- On it, Cap.

15:09.024 --> 15:10.235
These are the last
of the walking wounded

15:10.237 --> 15:11.682
from the bottom of this car.

15:11.684 --> 15:12.817
What's the word from up top?

15:12.819 --> 15:14.519
Two dead, one trapped so far.

15:14.521 --> 15:16.821
JANET: Captain Nash, search
dog detail just landed.

15:16.823 --> 15:18.122
Can you spare a couple medics?

15:18.125 --> 15:19.529
All right, Hen, Chim, go with them.

15:19.532 --> 15:20.864
Are you sure, Cap?

15:20.867 --> 15:22.793
(METAL SCREECHING)

15:22.796 --> 15:24.962
(ALL GRUNTING)

15:24.964 --> 15:26.931
<i>♪</i>

15:26.933 --> 15:29.039
We need all the paramedics
we have on the ground.

15:29.042 --> 15:31.242
What about up there?

15:31.245 --> 15:33.004
BOBBY: I got it.

15:33.006 --> 15:39.378
<i>♪</i>

15:47.020 --> 15:50.021
(METAL CREAKING)

15:50.023 --> 15:52.723
<i>♪</i>

15:52.725 --> 15:54.405
(GRUNTS) You got it, Buck?

15:54.408 --> 15:55.793
All right.

15:55.795 --> 16:00.453
<i>♪</i>

16:00.456 --> 16:02.599
He's got a collapsed
lung from the blunt force.

16:02.602 --> 16:03.734
O2 levels are dropping.

16:03.736 --> 16:05.036
I can relieve the pressure,

16:05.038 --> 16:06.938
but we gotta move this beam off him.

16:06.940 --> 16:08.802
(GRUNTS) Still too heavy.

16:08.805 --> 16:10.079
It's not gonna budge.

16:10.082 --> 16:12.022
All right. Let's try the hydraulic ram.

16:14.414 --> 16:16.314
- Got it, Buck?
- Yeah.

16:16.316 --> 16:19.317
- (GRUNTS)
- (METAL CREAKS)

16:19.319 --> 16:22.854
<i>♪</i>

16:22.856 --> 16:24.522
(GEORGIA SCREAMING)

16:24.524 --> 16:26.057
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa! Hey!

16:26.059 --> 16:27.199
We got somebody else!

16:27.202 --> 16:28.392
(GRUNTING)

16:28.394 --> 16:32.029
<i>♪</i>

16:32.031 --> 16:33.898
- (GASPING)
- EDDIE: How you doing?

16:33.900 --> 16:37.268
(GROANS) My side really hurts.

16:37.270 --> 16:39.203
I'm gonna take a peek.

16:39.205 --> 16:44.976
<i>♪</i>

16:44.978 --> 16:47.778
Oh.

16:47.780 --> 16:50.772
Force of the crash pushed
her leg up into her torso.

16:50.775 --> 16:52.274
What? (GASPING)

16:52.277 --> 16:53.851
It's gonna hurt a little bit.

16:53.853 --> 16:55.653
(WHIMPERS)

16:55.655 --> 16:56.687
All right.

16:56.689 --> 16:57.989
(SCREAMS)

16:57.991 --> 17:01.559
(WHIMPERING)

17:01.561 --> 17:03.661
There's still a pulse in her foot.

17:03.663 --> 17:06.297
Blood's still pumping to her.

17:06.299 --> 17:08.566
All right. That's a beam.

17:08.568 --> 17:10.734
- Come on.
- Be right back, okay?

17:10.737 --> 17:13.436
Okay.

17:13.439 --> 17:16.440
(BOTH GRUNTING)

17:16.442 --> 17:18.376
Hey. What's going on?

17:18.377 --> 17:20.211
They're both trapped by the same beam.

17:20.213 --> 17:23.414
We take the pressure off of
him and we're squeezing her.

17:23.415 --> 17:24.998
Which one has the better shot?

17:25.001 --> 17:26.782
Injuries are different.

17:26.786 --> 17:29.187
The risk is the same.

17:29.189 --> 17:32.256
What are we saying? We
gotta pick who we save?

17:32.259 --> 17:34.358
I'm saying I don't think
we can save 'em both.

17:34.360 --> 17:37.629
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSICAL FLOURISH)</i>

17:46.219 --> 17:48.353
Now, it'll be hard on Alexis

17:48.355 --> 17:49.921
because she's still struggling

17:49.923 --> 17:52.190
with admitting that it even happened.

17:52.192 --> 17:54.259
Well, it's not uncommon

17:54.261 --> 17:57.762
for victims to distance
themselves from the crime.

17:57.764 --> 18:00.802
Yeah. Now, Michelle.

18:00.805 --> 18:03.401
I think she'll be great on the stand

18:03.403 --> 18:05.970
but she is the one that
I worry about the most.

18:05.972 --> 18:07.305
Why is that?

18:07.307 --> 18:09.841
All of her statements are peppered with,

18:09.843 --> 18:11.155
"I should've known."

18:11.158 --> 18:13.278
"I should have realized."

18:13.280 --> 18:15.713
She blames herself.

18:15.715 --> 18:17.448
(SIGHS)

18:17.450 --> 18:21.619
Thinks if she had done
something differently,

18:21.621 --> 18:23.688
maybe it wouldn't have happened.

18:23.690 --> 18:26.824
Yeah. Right.

18:26.826 --> 18:29.527
I can't help but notice
that there's a file missing

18:29.529 --> 18:30.728
from this table.

18:30.730 --> 18:33.798
<i>(SERIOUS MUSIC)</i>

18:33.800 --> 18:37.402
<i>♪</i>

18:37.404 --> 18:38.670
(SIGHS)

18:38.672 --> 18:40.238
His attack on me

18:40.240 --> 18:42.941
was nothing like what he
did to these other women.

18:42.943 --> 18:45.977
<i>♪</i>

18:45.979 --> 18:48.301
Now, your priority should be them.

18:48.304 --> 18:52.450
I don't think it's
fair to compare traumas.

18:52.452 --> 18:53.851
And from what I read,

18:53.853 --> 18:56.821
his attack on you was pretty brutal.

18:56.823 --> 18:58.152
Well, it happened pretty fast

18:58.155 --> 19:00.358
and I don't remember most of it.

19:00.360 --> 19:03.261
Everyone says I'm lucky that I don't.

19:03.263 --> 19:05.430
They're wrong.

19:05.432 --> 19:08.900
Yes, sometimes the brain's
way of protecting us

19:08.902 --> 19:12.338
is to block out painful memories.

19:13.907 --> 19:15.740
But I've been doing this a long time

19:15.742 --> 19:18.176
and I have never had anyone feel better

19:18.178 --> 19:21.312
because they didn't know
what happened to them.

19:21.314 --> 19:23.481
You were never here

19:23.483 --> 19:26.317
to talk about these other women.

19:26.319 --> 19:27.852
Were you?

19:27.854 --> 19:30.154
<i>♪</i>

19:30.156 --> 19:31.723
I'm here for you.

19:31.725 --> 19:38.630
<i>♪</i>

19:38.632 --> 19:40.431
Well, I'm not ready.

19:40.433 --> 19:47.339
<i>♪</i>

19:48.742 --> 19:50.642
I'll leave this here

19:50.644 --> 19:51.909
for when you are.

19:51.911 --> 19:56.681
<i>♪</i>

19:56.683 --> 19:59.450
<i>(TENSE MUSIC)</i>

19:59.452 --> 20:05.824
<i>♪</i>

20:11.431 --> 20:13.431
(MAN GRUNTING)

20:13.433 --> 20:15.700
MEDIC: All right, hold on. Here we go.

20:15.702 --> 20:19.003
<i>♪</i>

20:19.005 --> 20:20.672
TODD: Milo!

20:20.674 --> 20:22.901
<i>♪</i>

20:22.904 --> 20:24.075
Help!

20:24.077 --> 20:25.910
Sir, are you hurt?

20:25.912 --> 20:27.957
No. I'm looking for my son.

20:27.960 --> 20:29.981
Hey, do you know where he
was when the train crashed?

20:29.983 --> 20:32.291
He was in the RV.

20:32.294 --> 20:34.075
I left him when I was talking to Rory.

20:34.078 --> 20:35.420
All right, tell us about your son.

20:35.422 --> 20:37.388
He's 15.

20:37.390 --> 20:40.904
Black hair, green shirt.

20:40.907 --> 20:42.893
Do you have anything
with his scent on it?

20:42.896 --> 20:44.028
Maybe help us track him?

20:44.030 --> 20:45.323
No, I don't.

20:45.326 --> 20:47.097
Oh, wait, wait, wait, wait.

20:47.100 --> 20:48.599
Milo used this to clean his hands,

20:48.601 --> 20:50.302
but it's gotta have
antifreeze or coolant on it.

20:50.304 --> 20:52.358
That's okay, Richard's trained
to track only human scents.

20:52.360 --> 20:54.604
Chemicals don't confuse
him. What you got buddy?

20:54.607 --> 20:56.307
- What you got?
- (DOG BARKS)

20:56.309 --> 20:58.676
<i>♪</i>

20:58.678 --> 21:01.312
All right, Sam. This is for the pain.

21:01.314 --> 21:03.514
<i>♪</i>

21:03.516 --> 21:05.983
Keep him talking.

21:05.985 --> 21:08.019
(METAL CREAKING)

21:08.021 --> 21:12.857
<i>♪</i>

21:12.859 --> 21:15.193
It's her...

21:15.195 --> 21:17.929
or me, isn't it?

21:17.931 --> 21:19.864
No.

21:19.866 --> 21:22.767
No, that's not what we do.

21:22.769 --> 21:24.769
So tell me about your fiancée.

21:24.771 --> 21:26.437
When's the wedding?

21:26.439 --> 21:29.474
June.

21:29.476 --> 21:31.943
She wants to wait...

21:31.945 --> 21:33.903
till the girls are done with school.

21:33.906 --> 21:36.314
You're a father.

21:36.316 --> 21:37.715
Yeah.

21:37.717 --> 21:39.784
(DISTANT SIRENS WAILING)

21:39.786 --> 21:42.053
Tess...

21:42.055 --> 21:43.258
Natalie.

21:43.261 --> 21:48.593
<i>♪</i>

21:48.596 --> 21:50.463
BRENDAN: Good boy, Richard. Good boy.

21:50.466 --> 21:51.698
(DOG BARKING)

21:51.701 --> 21:52.897
Milo.

21:52.899 --> 21:55.061
Sir, stand back so we
can do our work, okay?

21:55.064 --> 21:58.803
<i>♪</i>

21:58.805 --> 22:00.171
HEN: Milo, can you hear me?

22:00.173 --> 22:01.272
Yeah.

22:01.274 --> 22:03.074
- Dad?
- Right here, son.

22:03.077 --> 22:04.147
We're gonna get you out.

22:04.150 --> 22:05.432
You're lying very still, Milo.

22:05.435 --> 22:06.659
Is it because you're afraid

22:06.662 --> 22:08.641
or because you're having trouble moving?

22:08.644 --> 22:10.881
I don't think I can move.

22:10.884 --> 22:13.138
What's happening? Is
something wrong with him?

22:13.141 --> 22:15.119
Just give us a minute
to take a look, okay?

22:15.121 --> 22:17.755
Pulse is strong. Milo,
can you wiggle your toes?

22:17.757 --> 22:20.024
<i>♪</i>

22:20.026 --> 22:22.693
Normal reaction.

22:22.695 --> 22:24.695
C1 vertebra's intact,

22:24.697 --> 22:27.526
so I'm guessing it's not a spinal...

22:27.529 --> 22:30.096
but I can't seem to locate
the occiput ligaments.

22:30.099 --> 22:32.170
Atlanto-occipital dislocation?

22:32.172 --> 22:33.571
I've seen it in car accidents.

22:33.573 --> 22:35.840
Never seen someone still talking after.

22:35.842 --> 22:37.909
All right, Command, we
need an extraction team

22:37.911 --> 22:39.777
on the north side of train car two

22:39.779 --> 22:41.997
with a straight shot
to a medevac copter.

22:42.000 --> 22:43.784
And contact the children's hospital.

22:43.787 --> 22:45.448
Have them prep the neurosurgery OR.

22:45.451 --> 22:47.018
Wait, wait, wait, wait, what's going on?

22:47.020 --> 22:48.970
- She said it wasn't a spinal...
- Stand back.

22:48.973 --> 22:50.555
It's called an internal decapitation.

22:50.557 --> 22:51.989
His spine is intact.

22:51.991 --> 22:54.091
It's just no longer
connected to his skull.

22:54.093 --> 22:56.093
But he's alive. He's talking.

22:56.095 --> 22:57.695
As long as his spine remains intact,

22:57.697 --> 22:59.709
he's still got a good
shot of surviving this.

22:59.712 --> 23:01.279
We just need to get him to a hospital

23:01.282 --> 23:04.100
so the surgeons can
reattach his ligaments, okay?

23:04.103 --> 23:06.192
We need to find a way
to cool our saline,

23:06.195 --> 23:08.639
preserve as much nerve
and tissue as possible.

23:08.641 --> 23:10.341
Right. I saw an ice cooler over here.

23:10.343 --> 23:11.642
I'll get some ice.

23:11.644 --> 23:14.846
<i>♪</i>

23:14.848 --> 23:16.981
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

23:16.983 --> 23:21.519
<i>♪</i>

23:21.521 --> 23:24.388
(GRUNTING)

23:24.390 --> 23:26.157
Okay, I'm calling it.

23:26.159 --> 23:28.993
We start with the girl, we get her out.

23:28.995 --> 23:30.261
- Copy that.
- BUCK: No.

23:30.263 --> 23:31.596
It's gonna crush Sam's other lung.

23:31.598 --> 23:33.731
- He's gonna die.
- I am aware of that.

23:33.733 --> 23:35.366
The protocol dictates

23:35.368 --> 23:37.431
that we save whomever
has the better chance

23:37.434 --> 23:38.903
and Eddie's saying that's the girl.

23:38.905 --> 23:40.137
No.

23:40.139 --> 23:41.505
Her vitals are stronger.

23:41.507 --> 23:43.273
He's starting to decompensate.

23:43.276 --> 23:44.741
- If we have to choose...
- We do.

23:44.744 --> 23:46.177
We can't move that steel beam.

23:46.179 --> 23:47.979
(RUMBLING)

23:47.981 --> 23:51.282
- (GEORGIA WHIMPERS)
- (SAM GRUNTS)

23:51.284 --> 23:53.217
Okay. Okay, you're right.

23:53.219 --> 23:54.952
The beam is steel.

23:54.954 --> 23:56.992
But the skin on this thing,
the skin is stainless.

23:56.995 --> 23:58.246
That's much thinner.

23:58.249 --> 24:00.109
I could go outside, I
could cut a piece out,

24:00.112 --> 24:01.325
pull the girl through,

24:01.328 --> 24:03.316
and that will buy us
enough room to save Sam.

24:03.319 --> 24:04.896
No. This car hasn't been secured.

24:04.898 --> 24:06.631
That's why we're working on the inside.

24:06.633 --> 24:08.458
If this thing topples,
we can ride it down,

24:08.461 --> 24:09.494
but if you're on the outside...

24:09.496 --> 24:10.768
Yeah, I know.

24:10.770 --> 24:12.770
I will be crushed by
100 tons of train car,

24:12.772 --> 24:15.239
and I know that is a lot
avier than a fire truck.

24:15.241 --> 24:16.674
- But Bobby...
- Buck, stop.

24:16.676 --> 24:18.202
All right, I know you made a promise.

24:18.209 --> 24:20.845
What promise?

24:20.847 --> 24:22.446
To his fiancée.

24:22.448 --> 24:24.482
I promised I would
bring him back to her.

24:24.484 --> 24:25.950
What?

24:25.952 --> 24:27.618
To Abby.

24:27.620 --> 24:29.307
His fiancée's Abby.

24:29.310 --> 24:30.688
Okay.

24:30.690 --> 24:32.823
No. Look, it's not just about her.

24:32.825 --> 24:35.052
Okay, he's a father.
He has two daughters.

24:35.055 --> 24:37.323
Stop. You're too close to
this. This is too risky.

24:37.326 --> 24:38.933
Well, I am willing to take the risk.

24:38.936 --> 24:40.965
It's not yours to take.

24:40.967 --> 24:42.900
You can't just rush into
any dangerous situation

24:42.902 --> 24:44.702
and assume it's gonna be okay.

24:44.704 --> 24:46.953
'Cause sometimes it's not
and I am tired of being

24:46.956 --> 24:48.456
on the wrong side of
those hospital visits.

24:48.458 --> 24:50.174
Bobby. I am not Athena.

24:50.176 --> 24:51.596
What did you just say to me?

24:51.599 --> 24:52.777
Enough.

24:52.779 --> 24:54.111
We don't have time for this.

24:54.113 --> 24:55.947
<i>♪</i>

24:55.949 --> 24:57.648
Buck, come on.

24:57.651 --> 25:01.275
<i>♪</i>

25:05.857 --> 25:08.974
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

25:08.977 --> 25:16.478
<i>♪</i>

25:16.481 --> 25:20.183
- (ATHENA SCREAMS)
- (BOTH GRUNTING)

25:20.185 --> 25:22.586
- (ATHENA CRYING OUT)
- (BONE SNAPPING)

25:22.588 --> 25:27.291
<i>♪</i>

25:29.394 --> 25:32.128
(SIRENS WAILING)

25:32.130 --> 25:33.797
<i>(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)</i>

25:33.799 --> 25:36.233
<i>♪</i>

25:36.235 --> 25:39.236
(PHONE BUZZING AND RINGING)

25:39.238 --> 25:46.143
<i>♪</i>

25:46.812 --> 25:48.445
Hi, sweetie.

25:48.447 --> 25:51.314
<i>TESS: Abby, are you with my dad?</i>

25:51.316 --> 25:53.283
- I'm not right now.
<i>- TESS: What's going on?</i>

25:53.286 --> 25:54.571
<i>Are you in LA yet?</i>

25:54.574 --> 25:55.707
<i>Dad hasn't texted.</i>

25:55.710 --> 25:57.153
<i>He always texts.</i>

25:57.155 --> 25:58.755
I know. I know.

25:58.757 --> 26:02.025
He does.

26:02.027 --> 26:03.960
There was an accident on the train.

26:03.962 --> 26:04.847
<i>TESS: What?</i>

26:04.850 --> 26:06.320
But I don't want you to be worried

26:06.323 --> 26:08.075
because your dad is in the best hands.

26:08.078 --> 26:10.144
<i>TESS: Is he okay?</i>

26:10.147 --> 26:17.053
<i>♪</i>

26:21.112 --> 26:23.698
Okay, we have to secure that car ASAP.

26:23.701 --> 26:25.081
We got injured people inside

26:25.083 --> 26:26.905
and it's been creaking
like it's ready to go.

26:26.908 --> 26:28.585
(METAL CREAKING)

26:28.587 --> 26:31.021
How we doing, Sam?

26:31.023 --> 26:34.691
(GROANS) Okay.

26:34.693 --> 26:36.418
How's the girl?

26:36.421 --> 26:37.994
EDDIE: She's hanging in there.

26:37.996 --> 26:41.298
<i>♪</i>

26:41.300 --> 26:43.199
I'm really sorry.

26:43.201 --> 26:44.701
For what?

26:44.703 --> 26:48.238
That you got hurt.

26:48.240 --> 26:49.940
You were really nice to me.

26:49.942 --> 26:51.655
Say, you're gonna miss your gig.

26:51.658 --> 26:53.476
(LAUGHS)

26:53.478 --> 26:55.712
Neither of you guys
are missing anything.

26:55.714 --> 26:57.614
We're getting you out.

26:57.616 --> 27:04.522
<i>♪</i>

27:09.220 --> 27:12.021
(METAL CREAKING)

27:12.030 --> 27:18.736
<i>♪</i>

27:22.007 --> 27:25.308
(METAL CREAKING)

27:25.310 --> 27:30.113
<i>♪</i>

27:30.115 --> 27:31.214
(GRUNTS)

27:31.216 --> 27:34.784
<i>♪</i>

27:34.786 --> 27:37.020
All right, send up the basket!

27:37.022 --> 27:39.789
(METAL CREAKING)

27:39.791 --> 27:46.697
<i>♪</i>

27:53.939 --> 27:55.739
All right, your turn, Sam.

27:55.747 --> 28:02.219
<i>♪</i>

28:03.815 --> 28:05.048
HEN: On three.

28:05.050 --> 28:08.318
One, two, three.

28:08.320 --> 28:12.155
<i>♪</i>

28:12.157 --> 28:13.356
Almost there, Sam!

28:13.358 --> 28:15.692
(METAL CREAKING)

28:15.694 --> 28:18.695
(GASPING)

28:18.697 --> 28:23.733
<i>♪</i>

28:23.735 --> 28:25.001
HEN: All right.

28:25.003 --> 28:28.505
<i>♪</i>

28:28.507 --> 28:31.708
It's gonna be a little cold.

28:31.710 --> 28:33.076
TODD: Afraid he's used to it.

28:33.078 --> 28:34.907
We aren't living in the RV by choice.

28:34.910 --> 28:36.746
What are you talking about, Dad?

28:36.748 --> 28:38.665
We're on an adventure.

28:38.668 --> 28:40.468
Hey, what do we always say?

28:40.471 --> 28:42.518
Maybe not the best thing
to say right now, kid.

28:42.521 --> 28:43.987
Keep your head up 'cause...

28:43.989 --> 28:47.424
(WHEEZING)

28:47.426 --> 28:48.858
What just happened?

28:48.860 --> 28:50.960
The automatic signals from Milo's brain

28:50.962 --> 28:52.328
stopped telling him to breathe.

28:52.330 --> 28:53.630
We need to put a tube down his throat.

28:53.632 --> 28:55.131
Administering succinylcholine.

28:55.133 --> 28:56.933
This will stop the gag reflex.

28:56.935 --> 29:03.741
<i>♪</i>

29:04.890 --> 29:07.043
- CHIMNEY: I'll hold him steady.
- HEN: All right.

29:07.045 --> 29:13.617
<i>♪</i>

29:22.327 --> 29:24.127
All right.

29:24.129 --> 29:29.165
<i>♪</i>

29:29.167 --> 29:30.567
Easy.

29:30.569 --> 29:35.438
<i>♪</i>

29:35.440 --> 29:37.540
Inflating balloon to keep steady.

29:37.542 --> 29:41.211
<i>♪</i>

29:41.213 --> 29:43.379
Okay, switch.

29:43.382 --> 29:50.288
<i>♪</i>

29:54.459 --> 29:55.959
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

29:55.961 --> 29:57.293
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

29:57.295 --> 29:59.796
Abby? Is she here?

29:59.798 --> 30:01.731
She's down there waiting for you, Sam.

30:01.733 --> 30:07.036
<i>♪</i>

30:07.038 --> 30:10.039
<i>(HOPEFUL MUSIC)</i>

30:10.041 --> 30:16.547
<i>♪</i>

30:19.618 --> 30:21.484
Medevac's here.

30:21.486 --> 30:24.154
Airway's patent.

30:24.156 --> 30:26.623
Okay, what does that mean?

30:26.625 --> 30:30.693
It means he's gonna be okay.

30:30.695 --> 30:33.363
Because she's brilliant.

30:33.365 --> 30:34.724
Way to go, Wilson.

30:34.727 --> 30:38.268
<i>♪</i>

30:38.270 --> 30:39.502
You talk to the girls?

30:39.504 --> 30:41.538
You're so amazing and brave.

30:41.540 --> 30:43.072
They're gonna be really proud of you.

30:43.074 --> 30:44.607
Hey. Hey, man.

30:44.609 --> 30:45.975
Thank you.

30:45.977 --> 30:47.744
Buck.

30:47.746 --> 30:50.780
Thank you.

30:50.782 --> 30:53.950
You're Buck?

30:53.952 --> 30:55.852
Good to meet you, Sam.

30:55.854 --> 30:59.856
<i>♪</i>

30:59.858 --> 31:02.959
<i>(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)</i>

31:02.961 --> 31:09.166
<i>♪</i>

31:12.337 --> 31:13.536
You okay?

31:13.538 --> 31:16.673
<i>♪</i>

31:16.675 --> 31:18.141
What's next?

31:18.143 --> 31:25.115
<i>♪</i>

31:30.912 --> 31:34.213
I told you I don't remember
much about being attacked.

31:34.215 --> 31:37.651
It was behind me, and then
all of a sudden, it gets hazy.

31:38.653 --> 31:41.087
The next clear memory I have

31:41.089 --> 31:43.089
is being in the back of the ambulance

31:43.091 --> 31:45.125
and the look on my husband's face.

31:46.294 --> 31:48.694
I thought I was dying

31:48.696 --> 31:50.796
because he thought I was.

31:50.798 --> 31:52.331
But you didn't.

31:52.333 --> 31:54.633
You survived.

31:54.635 --> 31:56.402
But I shouldn't have.

31:56.404 --> 31:59.443
He had me dead to rights.

31:59.446 --> 32:00.611
Came up behind me.

32:00.614 --> 32:02.414
I didn't even know he was there.

32:02.417 --> 32:05.243
I've been a police officer for 30 years.

32:05.246 --> 32:07.713
I love my job and I'm good at what I do

32:07.715 --> 32:11.302
because I've always been
able to trust my gut.

32:11.305 --> 32:12.770
But now?

32:12.773 --> 32:14.452
You're doubting yourself.

32:14.455 --> 32:15.988
I should've called for backup

32:15.990 --> 32:18.157
before I went inside.

32:18.159 --> 32:19.464
Maybe.

32:19.467 --> 32:21.224
But that doesn't mean
that what he did to you

32:21.226 --> 32:22.225
was your fault.

32:22.228 --> 32:23.656
Maybe not,

32:23.659 --> 32:25.664
but I scared the hell out of my family

32:25.666 --> 32:27.325
and myself.

32:27.328 --> 32:28.861
And now I'm left feeling

32:28.864 --> 32:32.003
like I can't trust my instincts anymore.

32:32.006 --> 32:34.373
How the hell am I supposed
to go back out there

32:34.375 --> 32:35.908
feeling like this?

32:35.910 --> 32:38.911
You're not going back
out there tomorrow.

32:38.913 --> 32:40.946
<i>(EMOTIONAL MUSIC)</i>

32:40.948 --> 32:44.316
It'll take time to heal.

32:44.318 --> 32:47.747
But if that part of me never does?

32:49.123 --> 32:51.357
And that's why I was struggling.

32:51.359 --> 32:54.389
I couldn't figure out
what to say to you.

32:54.392 --> 32:57.096
How to make you understand
what you did to me

32:57.098 --> 32:59.064
and to the people I care about.

32:59.066 --> 33:01.167
<i>♪</i>

33:01.169 --> 33:03.702
But then I realized I don't have to.

33:03.704 --> 33:07.006
Because I'm gonna walk
out of this courthouse

33:07.008 --> 33:09.875
and I'm gonna have
some drinks with friends

33:09.877 --> 33:11.877
and you're gonna go sit in a box.

33:11.879 --> 33:14.079
<i>♪</i>

33:14.081 --> 33:16.373
Every morning, you will wake up

33:16.376 --> 33:19.544
and think about why you're there.

33:19.547 --> 33:22.420
You will have to think of me.

33:22.423 --> 33:24.957
<i>♪</i>

33:24.959 --> 33:29.195
But I can choose to never
think about you again.

33:29.197 --> 33:32.759
<i>♪</i>

33:32.762 --> 33:34.128
Are you sure?

33:34.131 --> 33:35.730
I don't like to brag,

33:35.733 --> 33:38.201
but I'm pretty good at
reading these things.

33:38.204 --> 33:41.029
The tumor has shrunk by almost 30%.

33:42.844 --> 33:45.658
Congratulations.

33:45.661 --> 33:47.279
This is...

33:47.281 --> 33:51.217
<i>♪</i>

33:51.219 --> 33:53.486
This is really happening.

33:53.488 --> 33:59.124
<i>♪</i>

33:59.126 --> 34:00.934
<i>ATHENA: It's a miracle.</i>

34:00.937 --> 34:04.496
You know, I think Dr. Burman
might be offended by that word.

34:04.499 --> 34:06.031
Thank you so much.

34:06.033 --> 34:09.400
But I am feeling pretty
miraculous myself.

34:09.402 --> 34:12.705
<i>I know it's not a clean bill
of health or anything, but...</i>

34:12.706 --> 34:15.373
It's good news, Michael. Be happy.

34:15.376 --> 34:17.243
<i>When do you wanna tell the kids?</i>

34:17.245 --> 34:18.710
Tonight.

34:18.713 --> 34:20.483
You know, we can tell 'em together.

34:20.485 --> 34:22.719
<i>ATHENA: Okay, what time?</i>

34:22.723 --> 34:24.540
Uh, you know, I'm not sure.

34:24.543 --> 34:26.951
There's something that I need to do.

34:26.954 --> 34:28.387
I'll call you later.

34:28.389 --> 34:30.464
<i>(UPBEAT MUSIC)</i>

34:30.467 --> 34:31.924
Hold the elevator!

34:31.926 --> 34:34.456
<i>♪</i>

34:34.458 --> 34:35.589
Hi.

34:35.703 --> 34:37.835
Hi.

34:37.839 --> 34:39.706
So where were we?

34:56.496 --> 34:57.830
Hi.

35:00.315 --> 35:01.647
Hi.

35:01.650 --> 35:05.490
Thanks for meeting me.

35:05.493 --> 35:07.359
How's... how's Sam?

35:07.361 --> 35:10.195
He's good.

35:10.197 --> 35:11.797
They're expecting a full recovery.

35:11.799 --> 35:14.087
Good. He seems like a great guy.

35:14.090 --> 35:16.282
He said the same thing about you.

35:17.972 --> 35:21.674
And I will never be
able to thank you enough

35:21.676 --> 35:23.108
for what you did.

35:23.110 --> 35:25.178
Just doing my job. That's all.

35:29.917 --> 35:32.735
I'm sorry that you had to
find out about it this way.

35:32.738 --> 35:37.088
I had actually wanted to
talk to you about everything

35:37.091 --> 35:38.424
while I was in town.

35:38.426 --> 35:39.959
That's what you're sorry for?

35:39.961 --> 35:41.864
<i>(EMOTIONAL MUSIC)</i>

35:41.867 --> 35:44.367
When did you know that you were...

35:44.370 --> 35:46.230
leaving me for good?

35:46.233 --> 35:48.679
- Well...
- You know, was it...

35:48.682 --> 35:53.371
was it in Morocco or
Paris or Dublin or...

35:53.374 --> 35:56.609
or did you know when
we were at the airport

35:56.611 --> 36:00.045
and I was kissing you
good-bye and promising you

36:00.047 --> 36:03.315
that I would wait for you?

36:03.317 --> 36:06.785
Did you know then that you
were never coming back to me?

36:06.787 --> 36:09.555
I thought I would.

36:09.557 --> 36:10.948
Look, I was a person

36:10.951 --> 36:15.260
whose life revolved around
everybody else's problems.

36:15.262 --> 36:18.464
I had no identity other than...

36:18.466 --> 36:20.833
the people that I was helping.

36:20.835 --> 36:23.703
My 9-1-1 calls, my dying mother.

36:25.606 --> 36:27.839
I just had no sense of self.

36:27.842 --> 36:32.077
I had to leave everything that I knew

36:32.079 --> 36:35.081
so that I could remember
who I actually am.

36:36.617 --> 36:38.854
And you did, right?

36:38.857 --> 36:42.126
I mean, you did remember, but...

36:43.991 --> 36:47.159
You still didn't come home.

36:47.161 --> 36:48.594
Yeah, I know.

36:48.596 --> 36:55.502
<i>♪</i>

36:57.144 --> 37:00.045
I think I was afraid
that if I came back,

37:00.048 --> 37:02.385
I would become that person again.

37:04.504 --> 37:07.639
Because I missed you.
I wanted to see you.

37:07.642 --> 37:11.010
But I didn't trust myself.

37:11.013 --> 37:13.514
Because being here,

37:13.517 --> 37:17.673
being with me,

37:17.676 --> 37:20.811
you might lose yourself again?

37:22.229 --> 37:24.162
Yeah.

37:24.165 --> 37:31.071
<i>♪</i>

37:36.177 --> 37:39.245
I'm glad to see you happy, Abby.

37:41.569 --> 37:43.535
You deserve it.

37:43.538 --> 37:50.444
<i>♪</i>

37:56.867 --> 37:59.479
<i>(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)</i>

37:59.482 --> 38:02.450
Oh, we are so proud of you, baby.

38:02.452 --> 38:05.353
My little girl, ready
to start a new chapter.

38:05.355 --> 38:06.888
You have your whole life ahead of you.

38:06.890 --> 38:08.189
So do you, Dad.

38:08.191 --> 38:10.758
(LAUGHTER)

38:10.760 --> 38:12.381
All right, all right!

38:12.384 --> 38:14.762
- To the graduate of 2020!
- (ALL CHEERING)

38:14.764 --> 38:17.065
Turn it up! Turn it all the way up!

38:17.067 --> 38:18.575
(LAUGHS)

38:18.578 --> 38:20.468
<i>♪ Share the spice of life ♪</i>

38:20.470 --> 38:22.370
<i>(EARTH, WIND & FIRE'S "LET'S GROOVE)</i>

38:22.372 --> 38:25.606
<i>♪ Baby, slice it right ♪</i>

38:25.608 --> 38:27.925
<i>♪ We're gonna groove tonight ♪</i>

38:27.928 --> 38:30.143
All right, buddy, your
turn. What do you wanna say?

38:30.146 --> 38:32.513
"May your dreams come true, May."

38:32.515 --> 38:36.217
Good. That's... that's really good!

38:36.219 --> 38:38.186
<i>♪ All right ♪</i>

38:38.188 --> 38:40.188
<i>♪ Let this groove set in your shoes ♪</i>

38:40.190 --> 38:42.390
So you excited about USC?

38:42.392 --> 38:43.725
I know your mom certainly is.

38:43.727 --> 38:45.827
Actually...

38:45.829 --> 38:47.276
do you have a minute?

38:47.279 --> 38:49.197
There was something I
wanted to talk to you about.

38:49.199 --> 38:51.733
Yeah, sure.

38:51.735 --> 38:54.302
Theoretically, Athena's
gonna be able to use this

38:54.304 --> 38:56.971
to light whatever that is?

38:56.973 --> 38:58.840
Right. It's a firepit.

38:58.842 --> 39:02.111
A firepit or a money pit?

39:03.179 --> 39:05.179
You know, it's gonna be great.

39:05.181 --> 39:07.982
<i>♪ Glide like a 747 ♪</i>

39:07.984 --> 39:09.150
- What is...
- It's greatness.

39:09.152 --> 39:11.486
You don't see the... greatness?

39:11.488 --> 39:13.413
No.

39:13.416 --> 39:14.615
(GASPS)

39:14.618 --> 39:15.717
You little brat!

39:15.720 --> 39:17.207
I'm gonna get you.

39:17.210 --> 39:20.227
<i>♪ Let this groove light up your fuse ♪</i>

39:20.230 --> 39:21.396
Ooh! (LAUGHS)

39:21.398 --> 39:22.730
Oh, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

39:22.732 --> 39:24.298
- It is a great party.
- Mm.

39:24.300 --> 39:25.566
Well, May deserves it

39:25.568 --> 39:27.568
and I had a little time on my hands.

39:27.571 --> 39:29.270
Well, you'll be back
to work soon enough.

39:29.272 --> 39:31.239
It's been 30 years since
I've been a civilian.

39:31.241 --> 39:32.407
I'm not sure you're ready

39:32.409 --> 39:34.108
to have me at home all the time.

39:34.110 --> 39:35.943
I think I could get used to it.

39:35.945 --> 39:37.512
Not that I'm gonna have the chance.

39:37.514 --> 39:38.980
I know you can't wait
to get back out there.

39:38.982 --> 39:41.849
Yeah.

39:41.851 --> 39:44.719
<i>(YAZOO'S "ONLY YOU")</i>

39:44.721 --> 39:47.555
<i>(UPBEAT SYNTH POP)</i>

39:47.557 --> 39:50.425
<i>♪</i>

39:50.427 --> 39:52.231
<i>♪ Looking from a window above ♪</i>

39:52.234 --> 39:53.728
Can I help?

39:53.730 --> 39:56.731
<i>♪ It's like a story of love ♪</i>

39:56.733 --> 40:00.201
<i>♪ Can you hear me? ♪</i>

40:00.203 --> 40:03.905
<i>MADDIE: People tend to fear the unknown.</i>

40:03.907 --> 40:06.076
<i>We look ahead, but we also look away.</i>

40:06.079 --> 40:08.310
_

40:08.313 --> 40:12.382
<i>Afraid of what terrible things
might be coming down the line.</i>

40:14.049 --> 40:16.850
<i>♪ All I needed for another day ♪</i>

40:16.853 --> 40:18.022
<i>MADDIE: We survive</i>

40:18.025 --> 40:20.759
<i>because we don't face our fear alone.</i>

40:20.762 --> 40:22.756
<i>We band together</i>

40:22.759 --> 40:25.159
<i>and we find strength in numbers.</i>

40:25.161 --> 40:27.061
<i>♪</i>

40:27.063 --> 40:29.931
<i>♪ Sometimes when I think of her name ♪</i>

40:29.933 --> 40:33.768
<i>♪ When it's only a game ♪</i>

40:33.770 --> 40:36.370
<i>MADDIE: Truthfully, the not-knowing,</i>

40:36.372 --> 40:39.107
<i>that's not something we should fear.</i>

40:39.109 --> 40:41.576
<i>It's something we should embrace.</i>

40:41.578 --> 40:45.813
<i>It's what makes this all
such a great adventure.</i>

40:45.815 --> 40:49.884
<i>♪ All I needed was the love you gave ♪</i>

40:49.886 --> 40:53.821
Hey, I just wanted to apologize.

40:53.823 --> 40:55.345
For the train.

40:55.348 --> 40:57.258
Look, it's all right.
We both got a little hot.

40:57.260 --> 40:59.594
You doing okay?

40:59.596 --> 41:01.496
(LAUGHS) Yeah.

41:01.498 --> 41:02.697
I think I am.

41:02.699 --> 41:04.412
<i>MADDIE: Because in this life...</i>

41:04.415 --> 41:06.567
- Good.
<i>- MADDIE: You have to be ready.</i>

41:06.569 --> 41:07.869
<i>For anything.</i>

41:07.871 --> 41:09.237
Whoa. That smells terrible.

41:09.239 --> 41:10.771
Well, it's the salmon
thing that you loved

41:10.773 --> 41:12.040
the last time you had it.

41:12.043 --> 41:13.940
I can't believe you're
still not feeling well.

41:13.943 --> 41:15.843
Have you seen the doctor?

41:15.845 --> 41:18.287
Oh, my God.

41:18.290 --> 41:19.447
We have to go.

41:19.449 --> 41:20.815
What? Why?

41:20.817 --> 41:22.450
Right now.

41:22.452 --> 41:25.052
<i>♪ And all I ever knew ♪</i>

41:25.054 --> 41:27.722
<i>♪ Only you ♪</i>

41:27.724 --> 41:28.890
Anything yet?

41:28.892 --> 41:30.391
MADDIE: Just give me a minute.

41:30.393 --> 41:32.560
It's already been over a minute.

41:32.562 --> 41:35.296
I mean, what is taking so long?

41:35.298 --> 41:37.398
I thought all you had
to do was pee on a...

41:37.400 --> 41:39.467
<i>♪ Can't take no more ♪</i>

41:39.469 --> 41:40.868
<i>♪ Wonder if you'll understand ♪</i>

41:40.870 --> 41:43.037
Oh, my God. Wait, are you sure?

41:43.039 --> 41:45.640
<i>♪ It's just the touch of your hand ♪</i>

41:45.642 --> 41:48.242
<i>♪ Behind a closed door ♪</i>

41:48.244 --> 41:50.305
You're pregnant?

41:50.308 --> 41:52.342
We're pregnant.

41:52.548 --> 41:54.614
We're pregnant.

41:54.617 --> 41:56.651
Yep.

41:56.653 --> 41:58.319
- We're having a baby?
- (LAUGHS)

41:58.321 --> 42:00.888
<i>♪ And all I ever knew ♪</i>

42:00.890 --> 42:02.944
<i>♪ Only you ♪</i>

42:06.907 --> 42:16.907
